##A family of three in Wuhan Leave Hospital, "a lifetime of sweating is over. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhu Xuan is a reporter for the paper

It's finally over!

As of Feb. 19, the wife, mother and Darling of Wuhan Resident Zhao Jiang had been discharged from the hospital after half a month of worry, bitterness and fear, and treatment in the isolation ward.

"When I didn't make it, I worried every day, " Zhao told The Paper news on Feb. 20. "It was a victory in stages. " After leaving the hospital, the three members of the family were still under quarantine in different places.

In early January, Lin Li, Zhao's wife, made preparations and bought masks and alcohol. On the 23rd, the city of Wuhan was "sealed off" . They did not even go down the building. But when Lin Li's mother in law came to visit, she coughed.

On the 27th, Lin Li was sore, and soon after, she began to have a fever.

On the 29th, she went to the hospital for a CT scan that showed an infection in her lungs; that day, Lin Li's family went in for a scan that showed that her son Tsutsu and his mother in law both had lung infections.

On February 1, Tsutsu was diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia.

To care for her 1 year old, Tsutsu, Zhao was placed in an isolation ward for 24 hours. He is not a good resistance, in the hospital accompanying this time, "vitamin C, Lotus Qingwen, antiviral oral liquid, gold leaf poison, protein powder are eating, try every two hours to drink 400 ml of water. "

In order to ensure the child's nutrition, in addition to milk powder rice noodles, but also prepared eggs, noodles, oats, meat paste, fruits and vegetables. When the Children Sleep, Zhao Jiang is basically cooking.

Zhao recorded Tsutsu's daily routine in the hospital room, there is also a new understanding of the doctor-patient relationship: "The medical staff is working hard. At the center of the Whirlpool, the staff and the people at the grass-roots level, only with more understanding can we go out together. "

On Feb. 13, Tsutsu recovered from his illness, and Zhao took him home. The mother-in-law recovered quickly and was discharged on February 19.

Lin Li, who spent 17 days in the Tianyou Hospital affiliated to Wuhan University of Science and Technology, thought he was the least ill. It wasn't until she saw the summary of her discharge that she realized she was the only one in her family with a severe illness and a combination of mycoplasma infection and the flu. At first, her condition is not stable, the middle appeared to have repeated fever, dyspnea and other conditions. On the day of the hormone and the antipyretic suppository, she felt that "a lifetime of sweating is over. ". The temperature dropped in the morning, but after a while, the body temperature climbed back above 37 degrees Celsius.

"My dad never cried. He cried when we got sick. If he collapsed, our family would really fall apart, " Lin Li said, "But I finally got over it. All the medical staff, family members, colleagues, friends and classmates gave me a lot of help and encouragement during this period. Thank you again! "

Tsutsu and her mother-in-law's recovery comforted Lin Li, who was determined not to be the "drag" but to work hard to recover. On February 19th, she was discharged.

The worst is over. At present, the three members of their family are separated in different parts of Wuhan, and they are all looking forward to the reunion.

Lin Li, Zhao Jiang, and Tsutsu are aliases

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
